  options = '[{"id":"A","text":"natural selection is a force that drives evolution, but it is not the only force.","is_correct":true,"explanation":"Choice A matches the question''s requirement and is consistent with the passage''s central claim or supporting detail. Re-read the sentences surrounding the key detail before eliminating this option on test day."},{"id":"B","text":"animals are passive participants in evolution.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"Choice B is incorrect because it either misreads the passage, overgeneralizes a limited detail, or focuses on information irrelevant to the question stem. Re-read the sentences surrounding the key detail before eliminating this option on test day."},{"id":"C","text":"animals are not necessarily the only factor that drives evolution.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"Choice C is incorrect because it either misreads the passage, overgeneralizes a limited detail, or focuses on information irrelevant to the question stem. Re-read the sentences surrounding the key detail before eliminating this option on test day."},{"id":"D","text":"evolution is a complex process that is not fully understood by scientists.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"Choice D is incorrect because it either misreads the passage, overgeneralizes a limited detail, or focuses on information irrelevant to the question stem. Re-read the sentences surrounding the key detail before eliminating this option on test day."}]'::jsonb,
  correct_answer = 'A',
  explanation = 'The author''s main point is that, while natural selection does drive evolution, it is not the only force at play. Animals are not simply passive participants, but also play an active role in shaping their own destinies and the evolution of their species. The passage states that "The author suggests that scientists are wrong to assume that animals evolved only in response to the environment. In thi…", which is the textual anchor for eliminating weaker choices. Choice A is correct because it aligns with that evidence: natural selection is a force that drives evolution, but it is not the only force.. Each incorrect option either contradicts a explicit detail, imports information not present in the text, or answers a different question than the one asked.',
